title: ASWA RANKINGS: Area nears season-long shutout
text:
Gary Cosby Jr./Decatur Daily Scamper 
Cullman’s Fletcher Jennings runs away from Decatur's Scott Littrell and Stephen Claborn during Friday's game. Posted: Tuesday, October 20, 2015 11:01 pm ASWA RANKINGS: Area nears season-long shutout Staff Reports cullmantimes.com 
Cullman has been no stranger to ranked opponents this season. Muscle Shoals, however, will be the Bearcats’ first from Class 6A. 
Non-region foes Etowah (5A) and Fayette County (4A) didn’t turn out to be much trouble. Don’t expect the same from the undefeated Trojans (8-0, 5-0), who held firm to their No. 4 spot in the Alabama Sports Writers Association’s latest prep football poll released late Tuesday night. Muscle Shoals has already wrapped up the Region 8 title and figures to be a handful. 
Another ranked team awaits Cullman (6-2, 3-2) in next Friday’s regular season finale. Russellville is up to eighth this week in 5A. 
Winless Holly Pond is in for a trip to Region 5 champ Winfield (7-1), which sits 10th in 3A. 
No teams from The Times’ coverage area have cracked their respective top 10s at any point this fall. 
See this week’s complete poll below: 
Class 7A

2. Spain Park (4) (7-1) 268

4. Central-Phenix City (7-2) 195
